{
  "answer": "**Manusmṛti 9.3** states the precise rule on a woman's dependence: her father protects her in childhood, her husband protects her in youth, and her sons protect her in old age; **a woman is never fit for independence**.[^1]\n\nThis is embedded in a broader discussion in Chapter 9 on the duties of men toward women, emphasizing lifelong protection to prevent misconduct and ensure family welfare (e.g., 9.2–6).[^2]\n\n[^1]: Manu, *Manusmṛti*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/09/translation/#p-233021).\n\n[^2]: Manu, *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 9, [Chapter](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/09/translation/).",
